<h1 class="x-h1">Accessibility</h1>

<div class="x-block-full">
    <p>Xooie relies on semantic relationships between elements.  When possible, Xooie roles are derived from <a class="x-link" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria/roles" target="_blank">ARIA roles</a>.  Even if your markup isn't 100% semantic, Xooie will add the appropriate attributes to make sure that the contextual relationships between elements are defined.  As a result, Xooie widgets are highly compatible with screen readers and other assistive technologies.
</div>

<div class="x-block-full">
    <h2 class="x-h2">How Xooie Makes Accessibility Easier</h2>

    <p>Determining which attributes to add to make a widget accessible can be inordinately complicated:</p>

    <pre><code>
        &lt;div&gt;
            &lt;ul role="tablist" aria-owns="tab-1 tab-2 tab-3"&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;

            &lt;button id="tab-1" role="tab" aria-controls="tabpanel-1" aria-selected="true"&gt;Header 1&lt;/button&gt;
            &lt;div id="tabpanel-1" role="tabpanel" aria-expanded="true"&gt;Content for header 1&lt;/div&gt;

            &lt;button id="tab-2" role="tab" aria-controls="tabpanel-2" aria-selected="false"&gt;Header 2&lt;/button&gt;
            &lt;div id="tabpanel-2" role="tabpanel" aria-expanded="false"&gt;Content for header 2&lt;/div&gt;

            &lt;button id="tab-3" role="tab" aria-controls="tabpanel-3" aria-selected="false"&gt;Header 3&lt;/button&gt;
            &lt;div id="tabpanel-3" role="tabpanel" aria-expanded="false"&gt;Content for header 3&lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
    </code></pre>

    <p>Xooie takes the complexity out of building accessible widgets by just defining roles.  When adding certain elements is non-intuitive, Xooie will render those elements for you:</p>

    <pre><code>
        &lt;div data-widget-type="tab"&gt;

            &lt;button data-x-role="tab"&gt;Header 1&lt;/button&gt;
            &lt;div data-x-role="tabpanel"&gt;Content for header 1&lt;/div&gt;

            &lt;button data-x-role="tab"&gt;Header 2&lt;/button&gt;
            &lt;div data-x-role="tabpanel"&gt;Content for header 2&lt;/div&gt;

            &lt;button data-x-role="tab"&gt;Header 3&lt;/button&gt;
            &lt;div data-x-role="tabpanel"&gt;Content for header 3&lt;/div&gt;
            
        &lt;/div&gt;
    </code></pre>

    <p>Nothing beats good old semantic markup, but Xooie takes the complication out of building rich, accessible widgets for the web</p>
</div>

